---
title: HiTicket - Sequence Diagram - User Registration
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant React as React Login UI
    participant API as Express API
    participant DB as MongoDB
    participant UserModel as User Model
    participant JWT as JWT Service

    User->>React: Submit { name, email, password }
    React->>API: POST /api/auth/register (authLimiter 10 req/15min per IP)

    alt Missing name, email, or password
        API-->>React: 400 - Name, email and password are required
    else All fields present
        API->>DB: User.findOne({ email })
        DB-->>API: existing user or null
        alt Email already registered
            API-->>React: 400 - Email already registered
        else Email is available
            API->>UserModel: User.create({ name, email, password, role: user })
            UserModel->>UserModel: pre save hook - bcrypt.hash(password, saltRounds 12)
            UserModel->>DB: INSERT user document (tokenVersion defaults to 0)
            DB-->>UserModel: saved user document
            UserModel-->>API: user object
            API->>JWT: jwt.sign({ id, tokenVersion: 0 }, JWT_SECRET, expiresIn: 30d)
            JWT-->>API: signed session JWT
            API-->>React: 201 { token, user: { id, name, email, role } }
            React-->>User: Store token in localStorage, navigate to home
        end
    end
